records.HealthCloudGA__Description__c:
EDUCATE: When to call the doctor for diabetes problems:
• 2 blood sugar readings in a row that are over 240
• Signs of high blood sugar (hyperglycemia)
• Signs of low blood sugar (hypoglycemia)
• Urine ketones are moderate to high, if your doctor is having you check them.
• Blood sugar readings are lower than the level your doctor says is OK.
• Problems checking your blood sugar or using the monitor
• Problems getting or taking your medicine
• Fever of 101 degrees F (38.3 degrees C) or higher for 12 hours
• Loose stools (diarrhea) for more than 6 hours
• Calluses, blisters, infections, or sores on your legs or feet

records.HealthCloudGA__Description__c:
EDUCATE: Advantages and disadvantages for patients considering CGM:
• Advantages include: they provide more real-time measurement (and therefore allow better blood
sugar control).
• Disadvantages include: they are not considered to be as accurate as a standard blood glucose meter
measurement.
